name:
Lower Bay Whale Waters
20 knot speed restriction
information:
20 Knot Speed Restriction and 1nm from shore course restriction. 

Lower Bay whale waters extend from a line drawn between Point Gustavus and Point Carolus to a line drawn between the northern tip of Strawberry Island to Lars Island. 

Unless other restrictions apply, operators may perpendicularly approach or land on shore (i.e., by the most direct line to shore) through designated whale waters, but they may not transit along the shore.

name:
Lower Bay Whale Waters 
1 nm from shore course restriction
information: Operating a motor vessel less than one nautical mile from shore (where the width of the water permits), or in narrower areas navigating outside of mid-channel is prohibited. This restriction does not apply to motor vessels less than 18 feet in length.

name: Johns Hopkins Inlet Harbor Seal Protection Area 10 kt
information:
Annual Closure/Restriction:

May 1 - June 30

Closed to all vessel traffic from the face of the Johns Hopkins Glacier to an imaginary line from Jaw Point due west.

July 1 - August 31

10 knot speed limit applies within waters of Johns Hopkins Inlet south of 58° 54.2'.

All vessels (including kayaks) must remain further than 1/4 nautical mile from any seal hauled out on ice, except when safe navigation requires, and then with due care maintain a 1/4/ mile distance from any concentration of seals.
